Just in theory it would be possible to get the number of enum values via the preprocessor:


```cpp
cat src/util/enum_class.h 
// Copyright (c) 2020 The Bitcoin Core developers
// Distributed under the MIT software license, see the accompanying
// file COPYING or http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php.

#ifndef BITCOIN_UTIL_ENUM_CLASS_H
#define BITCOIN_UTIL_ENUM_CLASS_H

#include <boost/preprocessor/variadic/size.hpp>

#define ENUM_CLASS(name, ...)        \
    enum class name { __VA_ARGS__ }; \
    constexpr size_t name##_##SIZE { BOOST_PP_VARIADIC_SIZE(__VA_ARGS__) }

#endif // BITCOIN_UTIL_ENUM_CLASS_H
```

This could be used to write

```cpp
static_assert(CONNECTION_TYPE_DOC.size() == ConnectionType_SIZE, "inconsistent docs");
```

Probably not worth the effort. Just saying that it is possible.

